GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 734
Short Title: Modernize Debt Settlement Prohibition. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Howard, Setzer, B. Jones, and Liu (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Judiciary 1, if favorable, Finance, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of
the House
April 3, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODERNIZE AND EXPAND THE PROHIBITION OF DEBT SETTLEMENT
3 BY MAKING DEBT SETTLEMENT AN UNFAIR TRADE PRACTICE, CLARIFYING
4 THE DEFINITION OF DEBT SETTLEMENT, EXPANDING CIVIL REMEDIES
5 AVAILABLE TO DEBTORS, AND LIMITING DEBT SETTLEMENT ACTS THAT ARE
6 AUTHORIZED AND TO MAKE OTHER ADMINISTRATIVE AND TECHNICAL
7 CHANGES.
8 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
9 SECTION 1.(a) Article 56 of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes is recodified as
10 Article 9 of Chapter 75 of the General Statutes as follows:
