1 "§ 75-155. Certain persons and transactions not deemed debt adjusters or debt
2 adjustment.Acts authorized.
3 The following individuals or transactions shall persons are not be deemed debt adjusters or
4 as being engaged in the business or practice of debt adjusting:adjusting or debt settlement:
5 (1) Any person or individual who is a regular full-time employee of a debtor,
6 debtor and who acts as an adjuster of his with respect to an employer's debts.
7 (2) Any person or individual acting pursuant to any order or judgment of a court,
8 or a court order.
9 (3) Any person acting pursuant to authority conferred by any a law of this State
10 or of the United States.
11 (3)(4) Any person who that is a creditor of the debtor, or an agent of one or more
12 creditors of the debtor, including the creditor's agent, and whose services in
13 adjusting the debtor's debts are rendered that acts without cost to the
14 debtor.debtor with respect to debts owed to the creditor.
15 (4)(5) Any person who that at the request of a debtor, debtor arranges for or makes
16 a loan to the debtor, debtor and who, at the authorization of the debtor, acts as
17 an adjuster of the debtor's debts engages in debt adjusting in the disbursement
18 of the proceeds of the loan, loan without compensation cost to the debtor for
19 the services rendered in adjusting such debts.the debts, except interest and fees
20 authorized by law.
21 (5) An intermittent or casual adjustment of a debtor's debts, for compensation, by
22 an individual or person who is not a debt adjuster or who is not engaged in the
23 business or practice of debt adjusting, and who does not hold himself out as
24 being regularly engaged in debt adjusting.
25 (6) An attorney-at-law licensed to practice in this State who is not employed by a
26 debt adjuster.and acting within the attorney-client relationship with the debtor
27 or creditor, excluding services provided to a debtor by an attorney, or in the
28 name of an attorney, who has entered into any arrangement with a person
29 engaged, directly or through affiliates, in debt adjusting or debt settlement.
30 (7) An organization that provides credit counseling, education, and debt
31 management services to debtors if the organization also does all of the
32 following:
33 a. Provides individualized credit counseling and budgeting assistance to
34 the debtor without charge prior to the debtor's enrollment in a debt
35 management plan provided by the organization.
36 b. Determines that the debtor has the financial ability to make payments
37 to complete the debt management plan and that the plan is suitable for
38 the debtor.
39 c. Disburses the debtor's funds to creditors pursuant to a debt
40 management plan that the debtor has paid for with no more than
41 nominal consideration and has agreed to in writing.
42 d. Charges no fee or a fee to cover the cost of administering a debt
43 management plan not to exceed forty dollars ($40.00) for origination
44 or setup of the debt management plan and ten percent (10%) of the
45 monthly payment disbursed under the debt management plan not to
46 exceed forty dollars ($40.00) per month.
47 d.e. Provides to the debtor, periodically and on no less than a quarterly
48 basis, an individualized accounting for the most recent period of all of
49 the debtor's payments and disbursements under the debt management
50 plan and all charges paid by the debtor.
